This paper is about relation extraction, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper proposes a deep learning model that integrates convolutional neural network (CNN) with a pairwise ranking framework, which is a common approach in machine learning (cs.LG). The model also introduces novel ranking loss functions, which is a contribution to the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the problem of class imbalance, which is a common issue in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, and cs.NE.
